                        "name": "peptolab",
                        "displayName": "Simon Mundy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This isn't really required. How it works is that:-\n\n* A $select object is instantiated, as you've noted above\n* When the __toString() method of the $select object is called, the object checks for a 'FROM' table\n* If one doesn't exist, it adds it, using the method described above, so any change to _name, _cols or _schema will be automatically added",
